text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia tetanophylla is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Great Southern, Goldfields-Esperance and Wheatbelt regions of Western Australia.The pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.6 to 2 metres (2 to 7 ft). It blooms from August to October and produces yellow flowers.
